- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as constraint satisfaction is a fundamental problem in AI and the paper discusses the application of relation algebras to this problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with computational problems and their complexity classification. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with algebraic structures and their applications to computational problems.
